Holland Public Schools is saddened to hear that former Holland High School and Hall of Fame swimming & diving coach Don Kimble passed away this morning. Kimble impacted the lives of countless student athletes, winning numerous MHSAA Division 2 state championships in both boys and girls swim programs during his time with the district.
Our thoughts are with his family during this difficult time. He will be missed by all who knew him.

post_text: Congrats to Dwayne "Tiger" Teusink on recently being inducted into the Western Michigan Tennis Association's Hall of Fame! Teusink, a graduate of Holland High School's Class of 1954 and a longtime teacher, tennis coach & athletic director at Holland Public Schools, was honored in 2016 when the district renamed the tennis complex at Holland High School after him. A well deserved honor for someone that has done so much for tennis at Holland High School, in our community, and across the state! #hpsProud #Alumni #ThankYou

post_text: Today, we remember and honor those who sacrificed their lives while serving our country, including our #Alumni and staff of Holland Public Schools. Across the district, flags have been lowered to the half-staff position. At Holland High School, a monument honoring the memory of those who gave their lives and whose lives were saved stands tall in the courtyard, dedicated to Holland High alumni Spencer Freestone ('65), Jack Elenbaas ('66) and Bruce Van Dam ('67) who all served and died in the Vietnam War. #NeverForget
text: Today, we remember and honor those who sacrificed their lives while serving our country, including our #Alumni and staff of Holland Public Schools. Across the district, flags have been lowered to the half-staff position. At Holland High School, a monument honoring the memory of those who gave their lives and whose lives were saved stands tall in the courtyard, dedicated to Holland High alumni Spencer Freestone ('65), Jack Elenbaas ('66) and Bruce Van Dam ('67) who all served and died in the Vietnam War. #NeverForget

post_text: Can you keep a secret?
shared_text:
Holland West Connections
May 23 at 7:13 PM ·

A SURPRISE Celebration for Mr. Elenbaas! The West family would like to honor Mr. Elenbaas for all his years of dedication to the students of HPS and help him celebrate in his RETIREMENT!

On Wednesday, May 27th, we will have a parade past Dave's house from 5:00 to 6:00. We cannot post his address so if you would like to join in, meet us at Christ Memorial at 4:45 and we will head over to his house at 5:00. Everyone must stay in their vehicle as you drive past his home.

We are encouraging everyone to write a letter or make a card thanking Dave for all his years of service and how he has impacted you as a student. We will have a bin to drop the letters/cards in as you drive by. Mr. Elenbaas does not know about this celebration but his wife does. Let's keep this a secret (he doesn't do Facebook).

I know Mr. Elenbaas will be touched by this outreach of love!

post_text: Flowers and Music: two things that make the world a better place. Support Holland Bands during their flower sale! Details below!
shared_text:
Bethany Van Oss
May 11 at 5:29 PM ·

Both Mrs. Van Oss’ (my mother-in-law and I) just picked up these beautiful hanging flower baskets from Kraker Greenhouse who is so graciously working with the Holland Bands, which allows us (the HPS 8th-12th Grade Bands) to still have our spring flower fundraiser! Here’s how it works!:

-The sale is on now and runs through the end of May
-Go online to the Kraker Greenhouses webpage at: www.krakergreenhouses.com
-Click on "Our Online Store" at the top of the page.
-Start browsing and purchasing your favorite hanging baskets or flats online
-Prior to checking out online, please add the name of your fundraiser you are supporting in the comments section-"HBPA Fundraiser"
-Go to Kraker Greenhouses (11921 68th Ave
Allendale, MI 49401) anytime in the month of May to pick up your order by following the directions on the attached flyer.

Thank you so much for your support of the Holland Public Schools Band Program and I hope you are all staying safe and healthy!

shared_text:
Holland Jefferson PTO
May 8 at 9:44 AM ·

Today's Staff Appreciation Shout Out goes to ALL of our Jefferson Staff! From Mrs. Curtis in the office to Miss Amie on the playground, there are so many staff members who care for our kiddos and our school. To our Instructional Assistants, Cafeteria staff, Grounds crew, Speech and Language Pathologists, In House supports, Parapros, Literature coaches, Librarian, Teacher Assistants, Tier 2 Providers, Playground assistants, GSRP Assistants, Social Workers, Kids Connection staff, Psychologist, OT, PT, DHHS worker, OCSN worker, GRBS, Secretary, Assistant Dean of Students, and of course our Principal- THANK YOU! Our school couldn't run without you!! You keep things going behind the scenes, and Jefferson wouldn't be the same without each one of your smiling faces.

To ALL staff- keep an eye out for a small gift from PTO in the mail. Know we love you, we appreciate you, and we thank you with all of our hearts. <3
